No, thats not the only question.  The other question is whether or not her life was her responsibility. <br>
<br>
I'm not going to deny your questioning of the operator tho, i mean, yea, its relevant too.<br>
<br>
However, the way you phrased your &quot;only&quot; question infact justifies his running her over.  The reason being that you threw into the question &quot;if she was not putting them into a life-threatening situation or interfering with a combat operation&quot;.  Firstly, it was a military operation being conducted, so that leads to arguing about &quot;combat operation&quot;, and secondly it was most definitely a life threatening situation.  She may not have had a bomb strapped to her, but that doesn't mean the threat isn't there.  Israel is in a state of war...she posed a threat.  That is fact, and that is something you have to deal with when you ask that kind of a question. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=radgen>Radgen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 629<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/03 5:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=498.topic&index=154>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://radgen.homestead.com/files/Radgen5.jpg height=150 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Question Count.  If a protester in THIS country is run over while trying to block a bulldozer.  (and this does happen here a lot, not the running over but the blocking :-P)  DO you doubt that said operator would NOT be in SERIOUS legal trouble?<br>
